programme.title: Baby ER
programme.desc: Joshua undergoes yet another operation, this time to correct a life-threatening hernia. Premature baby Thomas continues his remarkable fight back.

programme.title: Baby ER
programme.desc: Baby Cole, born with his organs outside his body, needs emergency surgery. Phoebe comes off her ventilator for a third time. The neighbors are out in force to welcome Thomas home for the first time.

programme.title: Baby ER
programme.desc: Tristan fights for air due to a defect in his windpipe. Baby Cole starts down the road to recovery. Phoebe might finally be able to go home after six months in the hospital.

programme.title: Baby ER
programme.desc: Doctors consider a tracheostomy as they search for a solution to Tristan's breathing problems. Twin Seaneen has an operation to remove a blockage in her intestines. Cole suffers a setback.

programme.title: Baby ER
programme.desc: Cole goes back in for more surgery. Doctors must work quickly when they discover that Tristan has a heart problem and could suffer a heart attack at any moment. Seaneen begins the road to recovery.

programme.title: Baby ER
programme.desc: Doctors are baffled when baby Cole stops responding to treatment. Newborn Edward's blood flow problems are making him become seriously ill. Twin Seaneen begins feeding again.

programme.title: Checkmate: Round 1
programme.desc: Learn about this year's ten top chess champions, who've gathered in Gozo in order to compete for a serious wad of cash and the honor of being crowned Checkmate Champion.

programme.title: Checkmate: Round 2
programme.desc: Players' individual styles are assessed during this round of the tournament, and strategies are put to the test. Tiger Hillarp Persson faces off against Wenjun Ju, and Nino Maisuradze squares off with Nigel Short.

programme.title: Checkmate: Round 3
programme.desc: The Grandmasters continue to compete for the trophy during day three of the tournament. Igor sits for a skirmish with Wenjun, and Arkadij takes on Jovanka. Irina and Richard challenge each other on the board, and Nino faces off against Elizabeth.

programme.title: Checkmate: Round 4
programme.desc: The competition really heats up as the championship draws closer and closer. Nigel and Wenjun bid for a win on the board, and Elisabeth tries to outmaneuver Tiger's forces.

programme.title: Checkmate: Round 5
programme.desc: Strategies are tested and the coveted trophy is almost within grasp. Elisabeth shouldn't be underestimated as she enters the arena against top seat Nigel. Richard and Tiger rumble on the board, and Arkadij straps on his boots for a brush with Wenjun.

programme.title: Checkmate: Final Rounds
programme.desc: Even the top seats aren't safe from the underestimated underdogs amongst these Grandmasters of chess. After a tense several days, the Tournament Final concludes with a clear victor. Who will walk away with the Checkmate Trophy?

programme.title: The Bomber
programme.desc: Part 6 of this epic tale of war, love, betrayal, and sabotage. When Andrey, Katya, and Linko crash land in the field of battle, they find themselves in a struggle for survival that test the bonds of friendship.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Sofia Central Prison, Sofia, Bulgaria
programme.desc: With a crumbling foundation fit for demolition, Sofia Central prison is inhospitable for anyone, including criminals. With multiple prisoner cells, bunks stacked 3 high and horrid isolation cells, prisoners live idly behind bars for 23 hours a day.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Miami, Dade County Jail Boot Camp, Miami, Florida, USA
programme.desc: The toughest divisions of the Miami Dade: Boot Camp gives minor offenders a chance to escape the prison through unforgiving drills and rules. To many it is a better alternative to The M-D County Jail where murderers and rapists have their own rules.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: In the 1990s, the Chupacabra spread fear into the hearts of Texans. While some debate whether it walks on two or four legs, everyone agrees on its fangs, claws and thorny spine. There was no physical evidence until a resident made a gruesome discovery.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: Louisiana’s Honey Island Swamp Monster has terrorized the inhabitants of the bayou for more than 30 years. This bipedal monster with piercing yellow eyes is estimated to stand over two meters tall, and weigh more than 300 pounds.

programme.title: Wild Albania
programme.desc: From the snowy foothills of the Dinaric Alps to the turquoise waters of the Adriatic coast, we discover the secrets of beautiful Albania as we soar over streams, rivers and great lakes in the company of a young eagle born in early spring.

programme.title: The Wild Pacific
programme.desc: The Pacific ocean covers one third of our planet, more than all of the continents combined. For over 200 Million years, it has teemed with life, built new species, powered weather systems and affects every animal on earth.

programme.title: Australia's Wild Places: The Australian Alps
programme.desc: It may come as a surprise to non-Australians that the island continent renowned for its flat plains and searing deserts has snow-capped mountains at all.

programme.title: Secrets of the Deep: Wrecksploitation
programme.desc: There are more than 3,000,000 shipwrecks in the world, each one with a unique story. The age-old battle between treasure hunters and archaeologists continues to rage as more and more of these wrecks are uncovered.

programme.title: Comfort Eating
programme.desc: Nick Helm bumps into Crazyhead star Susan Wokoma on the way to the same audition in Notting Hill and the pair arrange to catch up over Austrian Tapas at Kipferl, Mexican tacos from Taquieria and jerk chicken burgers at Boom Burger.

programme.title: Comfort Eating
programme.desc: Nick is joined by Ed Gamble for an Irn Bru pulled pork sandwich cooked by Danny 'Mad Chef' McLaren. Then, Nick gets competitive as they are taught how to make sushi at Nippon kitchen. After, theres time to sample some traditional Scottish delicacies.

programme.title: Helicopter ER: Big Falls, Bigger Breaks
programme.desc: The team spring into action when a 12-year-old boy falls 30 feet from a bridge, and a walker collapses in the Dales.

programme.title: Helicopter ER: Surprise Impalements
programme.desc: The team flies to the rescue of a driver whose car has been cut in half in a freak accident. Plus, a biker is catapulted into a wood and impaled on a branch, and a farmhand is attacked by his own cowherd.

programme.title: The Wheelchair President
programme.desc: At the height of war, President Franklin D. Roosevelt inspired millions with visions of a new and better post-war world. Set against the epic scale of World War II, Professor David Reynolds presents an intimate biography of a man who was burdened.

programme.title: Nixon in the Den
programme.desc: David Reynolds takes a fresh look at the controversial career and presidency of Richard Nixon. Reynolds argues that Nixon was genuinely successful as an international statesman. Yet behind the scenes, Nixon's diplomacy was a story of intrigue and rivalry.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Tent City Jail, Phoenix, Arizona, USA
programme.desc: Old army tents left over from the Korean War house prisoners instead of cells. The Sheriff is a hard man who refuses to spend any more than he has to on his prisoners. Harassment and humiliation is a part of everyday life at Tent City.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Antanimora Prison, Madagascar
programme.desc: Desperate overcrowding, rats, and disease come standard in Antanimora Prison. Surrounded by the capital Antananarivo, it's bursting at the seams. It was originally built for 800 prisoners, but now it contains more than 3,000 prisoners.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: In the forests of the Appalachians, there lives a rare and still unidentified creature. Physically imposing, with traits characteristic of wolves, bears and gorillas; this strange monster strikes fear into peoples hearts. Some think it a werewolf.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: A mythical snake-like creature lives in the waters of Lake Seljordsvalnet in Norway. The monster measures some 20 meters in length, with a greenish tint and a raised back; Named Selma, she has been terrifying residents of the lake since the 18th century.

programme.title: Caught on Camera: Making Money
programme.desc: Criminals make their money from taking yours. They take anything they can get their hands on, including cash out of ATMs. These scammers can clear you out in a matter of hours.

programme.title: Stone
programme.desc: A convicted arsonist looks to manipulate a parole officer into a plan to secure his parole by placing his beautiful wife in the lawman's path. Starring: Edward Norton, Milla Jovovich, Robert De Niro.

programme.title: Odd Thomas
programme.desc: In less than 24 hours, the city of Pico Mundo will awaken to a day of catastrophe. Odd, a fast food chef with the ability to see the dead and sense impending danger, discovers a dark secret about a stranger in his town. Feat: Willem Dafoe.

programme.title: Christmas in Wonderland
programme.desc: Starring Matthew Knight and Chris Kattan. Three children and their father move from California to Canada. When they go shopping at the mall, they find counterfeit cash, inadvertently help catch crooks, and make a discovery about Santa.

programme.title: The Flight Before Christmas
programme.desc: Starring Mayim Bialik and Ryan McPartlin. Two strangers offer to share the last remaining room at a bed-and-breakfast when a snowstorm strands their flight in Montana on Christmas Eve.

programme.title: Let Go
programme.desc: Featuring the king of comedy Kevin Hart, this hilarious, unconventional and heartfelt journey is all about love, loss and other felonies! Discontent parole officer Walter is struggling with the humdrums of married life.

programme.title: Wishin' and Hopin'
programme.desc: Based on the New York Times best-selling Christmas novel by Wally Lamb comes the new Christmas classic, starring Molly Ringwald and featuring Chevy Chase as the narrator.

programme.title: The Great Gilly Hopkins
programme.desc: A feisty foster kid's outrageous scheme to be reunited with her birth mother has unintended consequences. The film boasts remarkable performances and a message about hope and humanity which shines through. Feat: Kathy Bates, Glenn Close & Bill Cobbs.

programme.title: Novocaine
programme.desc: A dentist finds himself a murder suspect after a sexy patient seduces him & steals all of the drugs from his practice. Starring: Steve Martin, Helena Bonham Carter, Chelcie Ross, Scott Caan, Laura Dern, Lynne Thigpen.

programme.title: Solitary Man
programme.desc: A car magnate watches his personal and professional life hit the skids because of his business and romantic indiscretions. Starring: Michael Douglas, Susan Sarandon, Jesse Eisenberg, Danny DeVito, Mary-Louise Parker, Jenna Fischer.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Slime People
programme.desc: The crew puts Commando Cody on trial for crimes against reality after watching the sixth episode of Radar Men while slime monsters invade Los Angeles in The Slime People.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Moon Zero Two
programme.desc: Moon Zero Two: The crew stages their own moon landing pageant as they watch the film about an astronaut hired to capture an asteroid made of sapphires.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Rocket Attack U.S.A.
programme.desc: Rocket Attack U.S.A.: The crew watches the second chapter of The Phantom Creeps and a film about an American spy sent to the Soviet Union to investigate a missile attack.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Lost Continent
programme.desc: A military team sent to search for a lost rocket ends up trapped on a mountain inhabited by dinosaurs in Lost Continent.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: King Dinosaur
programme.desc: In King Dinosaur, the crew pokes fun as scientists are terrorized by snakes, bugs, and dinosaurs on a newly discovered planet.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Black Scorpion
programme.desc: Giant scorpions rise out of a volcano and attack Mexico in The Black Scorpion.

programme.title: Giant Spider Invasion
programme.desc: Mike and the 'bots suffer through The Giant Spider Invasion .

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: City Limits
programme.desc: Set in the future, a teenage gang battles a corporation for control of an abandoned city in City Limits . Crow sings a song devoted to Kim Cattrall and the guys try their hand at a City Limits trivia game.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Indestructible Man
programme.desc: In Indestructible Man, a violent criminal named Butcher Benson is executed and becomes indestructible when he’s brought back to life. Butcher seeks revenge against those who caused his execution.

programme.title: Rifftrax Shorts: The Calendar: How To Use It / Perc! Pop! Sprinkle!
programme.desc: The Calendar. Whether you choose a Far Side page-a-day, an Anne Geddes year-of-horror or Twelve Months of Lifeguards that May Be Used as Flotation Devices, one thing is certain: none of us know how to use the damn things. / Perc! Pop! Sprinkle!

programme.title: Demon Bat
programme.desc: From the stars of Mystery Science Theater 3000 comes RiffTrax, hilarious audio commentaries for your favorite - and not-so-favorite - movies!

programme.title: RiffTrax: Bloody Pit of Horror
programme.desc: Filmed in PSYCHOVISION, (which we hear Fellini used to shoot in), Bloody Pit of Horror is must see Italian horror at its cheesiest. Mike, Kevin and Bill brave the spider piñata and give it their bloody best.

programme.title: The Guy From Harlem
programme.desc: As you'd expect from the title, The Guy from Harlem is set entirely in Miami. It's the story of private eye and titular Guy, Al Connors, a man with a reputation.

programme.title: Reefer Madness - Three Riffer Edition: Reefer Madness: Three Riffer Edition!
programme.desc: Yes, Reefer Madness let the world know that even a single dose of marijuana caused insane laughter, enhanced skill at ragtime piano, the inability to avoid hitting old men with your car, and defenestration.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Prisoners of the Lost Universe: Prisoners of the Lost Universe
programme.desc: Prisoners of The Lost Universe: An electrician, a TV newswoman, and a mad scientist are transported to a dangerous parallel universe.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Tourist Trap: Tourist Trap
programme.desc: Capitalizing on the widely-publicized series of unsolved murders that occurred at the Liberace Museum in Las Vegas in the late 1970s*, Tourist Trap is a slasher film with all the classic elements.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Dinosaurus
programme.desc: Dinosaurus is a vintage 60's monster flick, complete with a caveman and drunk-looking stop motion dinosaurs.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Brainiac: Brainiac
programme.desc: Back in 1661, a Spanish baron in the middle of burning at the stake escaped by hitching a ride on a passing comet. And now he returns, 300 years later, a shapeshifting monstrosity bent on killing the descendants of those who wronged him as The Brainiac.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Curse of Bigfoot: Curse of Bigfoot
programme.desc: Well, we found it. The Santa and the Ice Cream Bunny of horror films. Read that again. Reflect on it. Maybe discuss it with your local librarian.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Terror at Tenkiller
programme.desc: From the stars of Mystery Science Theater 3000 comes RiffTrax, hilarious audio commentaries for your favorite - and not-so-favorite - movies!

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Invincible
programme.desc: While chasing the roaches on the roof, Oggy crashes on the ground. His head is as flat as a pancake, but when he stands up, he doesn't feel any pain and refuses Jack's help! Jack is convinced that Oggy has become an invincible super hero.

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Oggy and the Magic Smile
programme.desc: Oggy buys a cardboard smile in a joke shop. When he puts the cardboard smile on his face, he is immediately transformed into a muscular, super confident athlete! And everyone is hypnotized by the vibes he gives off. They cater to his slightest whim.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 10
programme.desc: Super-Noms are back! Join Om Nom and Om Nelle on a thrilling journey to fight the Evil Spider and his minions! Meet new characters, travel to peculiar locations and check out the new amazing gadgets that Professor has invented!

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 11
programme.desc: Super-Noms like attending different events, but somehow an adventure awaits wherever they come ... Watch Om Nom and Om Nelle turn evil into good in this new season!

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 1
programme.desc: Om Nom, the hero of the world-famous Cut the Rope game series, is a cute little candy-eating monster. One day, he mysteriously shows up at the doorstep of one boy's house, and this marked the beginning of many fun adventures.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 2
programme.desc: Just when Om Nom thought all of the adventures are behind him and he can finally get some rest with the bowl of candies in hand, something unexpected happened ... Visit breathtaking locations and meet amazing new creatures in Om Nom Stories!

programme.title: Lucky Fred: San Juan Night / Braianna-Bot
programme.desc: Extraterrestrial moths are attacking the Earth, Brains must stop them and she will need Friday's help. / Fred wants to know what the girls' secrets are and orders Friday to pretend to be Brains to join their club ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Friday Gets Recalled / Fred's Game
programme.desc: Brains receives a new robot, the X-bot 9000, which is more sophisticated than Friday. But Brains gets quickly sick of the new model ... / Fred is chosen to be the goalkeeper at a football game but Wally K. is the striker for the other team ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Books and Roses / The Short Report
programme.desc: Today is Sant Jordi's Day and Fred wants to give Nora a rose. But there are ten other boys who have the same idea ... / A gossip blog publishes explosive photos of students at Fred's school – and now also details about aliens!

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Fred Gets Crushed / Dusty Rides Again
programme.desc: Braianna and Sir Percival are acting very strange. Fred suspects that they are dating ... / Friday is having a good time with his new robot friend Dusty. But one day his new buddy goes way too far ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Mister Perfect / Afternoon Off
programme.desc: Eddie is a talented sitar player who has enchanted Nora with his music. Fred is jealous and tries everything to win Nora over. / Brains bets with Fred that he can't spend a single afternoon without him.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Squirrel Scare / The Big Picture
programme.desc: Brains is terrified of squirrels and even programs a machine to suck them up ... / Mr. Fractal is confiscating Mort's phone including a picture of Brains fighting an alien!

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Unlucky Fred / Love Deodorant
programme.desc: Fred has lost his lucky dice in an amusement park. To find them again, he decides to turn Friday into a new pair of dice ... / Fred causes confusion with a perfume from space ...

programme.title: Supa Strikas: No 'El' in Team
programme.desc: After a mishap with the bumbling Professor, his coffee, and the state-of-the-art Match Measure Machine, things go horribly wrong with Shakes’ exercise plan!

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: The Ghastly Ghost
programme.desc: Marina wakes a pirate's ghost - who promptly moves in with her. She thinks he's funny at first, but the pirate soon wears out his welcome. How can you lay hands on a ghost and get rid of him? Fortunately, the pirate has a hermit-crab phobia.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Hundreds of Kids and Counting
programme.desc: Bernie adopts hundreds of cute little abandoned baby hermit-crabs. He builds them a little playground where they can hang out and play. But when Zig shows up to nab a few little toddlers for dinner, they don't turn out to be quite that cute.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Santa Zig
programme.desc: It's Christmas! Zig decides to dress up as Santa Claus and deliver a present to Marina (and grab her at the same time). But with his coconut palm sleigh and seals instead of reindeer, discretion is not the first word that comes to mind.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Goin' Home
programme.desc: Zig finds a book about African wildlife and realises that's where he actually comes from. He decides to go there and meet his compatriots. But hyenas are not very popular and no one is nice to him. Sharko and Marina miss him, and get depressed.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: The Return of the Crazy Dolphin
programme.desc: After a new series of unsuccessful attempts to make off with the mermaid, Zig decides to drop the whole thing and become a vegetarian. Even the wildest, most far-out inventions of Bernie aren't enough to prod him back into action.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Loony Cruise
programme.desc: Marina and Sharko board a luxury liner for a cruise disguised as humans... Zig and Bernie join as stowaways. When Sharko's identity is discovered, all humans leave ship. Bernie is assigned to the helm, while the usual chase takes place on board.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Bernie Moves House
programme.desc: An underwater volcanic eruption gives birth to a second island. Bernie, who has had an argument with Zig, decides to move there. While Zig has to fend for himself, Bernie builds a dream house, and parties it up with Sharko and Marina.

programme.title: The Wiggle's Present: Baby Antonio's Circus: Episode 4
programme.desc: Each episode of Baby Antonio’s Circus features Baby Antonio and his young friends who perform in his circus. In this episode: Ball Tricks / Juggling! Umbrellas! / Trapeze / Triangles / Ice Cream / Trapeze Fun / Trampoline Trucks.

programme.title: The Kingdom of Paramithi: Aladdin and His Magic Lamp / Goldilocks and the Three Bears
programme.desc: The King and Queen of Paramithi are so happy that they sing in the Royal Throne Room! / The King and Queen present The Medal of Paramithi to young Marcfranco for eating tasty vegetables every day.

programme.title: Grossology: The Insider
programme.desc: Ty personally stops the latest of Lance Boil's evil plans, the ex-grossologist villain decides to deal with Ty once and for all.

programme.title: Grossology: An Oldie but a Goodie
programme.desc: Abby gets bathed in a green ray that causes her to age 6000 times the normal rate!

programme.title: Grossology: Survival of the Grossest
programme.desc: It's science competition time at Ringworm jr. High!

programme.title: Grossology: School's Grossed Out For the Summer
programme.desc: Ty and Abby get left behind when they miss the bus for their class camping trip!

programme.title: Grossology: Vein Drain
programme.desc: People start showing up with bite marks on their necks, Ty and Abby can't help but wonder if maybe vampires aren't a myth after all.

programme.title: Grossology: Silent But Deadly - Part 1
programme.desc: Gassy super villain, Fartor returns with a scheme to fart-up the entire planet!

programme.title: Grossology: Silent But Deadly - Part 2
programme.desc: Fartor and his new apprentice, Far-Ty join forces to drill into the planet core and turn the earth into one big gas planet.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Training Trap
programme.desc: To boost sales of Cool Joe’s new line of boots, Supa Strikas must wear them for upcoming clashes. But Invincible United’s Vince is up to his usual tricks.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Super Skarra
programme.desc: An Invincible United henchman bungles a reconnaissance mission into Strikas’ training compound, trapping Shakes and El Matador in a security lockdown!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Spaceballs
programme.desc: Invincible United’s unscrupulous striker, Skarra, kidnaps the Professor and forces the fitness genius to help him outdo his enemies.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: El Sound Of Silencio
programme.desc: Supa Strikas are annihilated by Orion’s amazing airborne moves. Coach takes them to a space facility to train in a magnetic levitation chamber.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Amal Three's a Crowd
programme.desc: Rival team, Invincible United, orchestrate a fan ban for upcoming Supa Strikas matches! El Matador doesn’t think it’s a big deal, but come crunch time, he cannot perform in the empty stadium!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Bad Altitude
programme.desc: Supa Strikas get the fright of their lives upon hearing that Sultans have signed famed triplets, the Amal 3. They are said to have a psychic connection that cannot be beaten!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Dancing Rasta On a Ice
programme.desc: In their bid to raise the Super League trophy, the world’s greatest soccer team, Supa Strikas, must adventure through the world of soccer.

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Little Tom Oggy
programme.desc: Oggy is walking home with his shopping cart full of food. But finding his house becomes an impossible task since all the streets look alike! So he decides to leave a trail of groceries behind him, like little Tom Thumb to guide him self home.

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Mind the Giant!
programme.desc: Marky suddenly starts growing uncontrollably. Pretty soon he is even bigger than the house and just can't get enough to eat. He is going to loot and pillage the city for food. The police are on the lookout for the thief. Oggy has to hide the roach.

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Airship House
programme.desc: Everything is ready for Jack's birthday party but the roaches blow up all the hot air balloons with helium and release them in the attic. They stick to the ceiling and suddenly, the house takes off and floats into the sky like a huge dirigible.

programme.desc: In the climactic conclusion to the first round of the World Racing Grand Prix, Yusei must figure out a way to defeat Team Catastrophe's captain before all the cards in his deck disappear.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Party Crashers
programme.desc: After snatching victory from the jaws of defeat in the first round of the World Racing Grand Prix, Team 5D's celebrates their win and prepares for their next opponent Team Catastrophe.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Knight Takes Pawn
programme.desc: In the second round of the World Racing Grand Prix, Crow of Team 5D's gets set to take on Team Catastrophe's Herman. Can Crow swoop in and swipe all of Herman's life points?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Rook Takes Knight
programme.desc: With his life points on the line, Crow of Team 5D's looks to give Herman's Hook the Hidden Knight the heave-ho before it ruins his Runner and catapults Team Catastrophe into the next round.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Primos Plan: Part I
programme.desc: Primo and his Duel Bot Army crash the World Racing Grand Prix, putting the tournament and New Domino City in jeopardy.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Primos Plan: Part II
programme.desc: Primo decides to take matters into his own hands by challenging Yusei Fudo to a duel after watching Yusei interfere with his Duel Bot Army's mission of mechanized mayhem.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Primos Plan: Part III
programme.desc: Hoping to stop New Domino City from spiraling into total chaos, Yusei takes on Primo and his Meklord Emperors' debilitating ability to absorb Synchro Monsters.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Primos Plan: Part IV
programme.desc: With the safety of New Domino City hanging in the balance and Primo in control of Stardust Dragon, Yusei must figure out a way to get his go-to card back before his life points hit zero.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Primos Plan: Part V
programme.desc: It's the climactic conclusion to the battle between Yusei and Primo! Can Yusei defeat this menace and save his City, or will Primo prevail and send New Domino spiraling into chaos?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Eyes on the Prize
programme.desc: Yusei and Team 5D's get set to take on Team Ragnarok and their powerful Nordic Gods  Thor, Loki and Odin!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Duel for Redemption
programme.desc: When Jack is informed by Team Ragnarok's Dragan that Director Goodwin fixed the match they had years earlier, Jack begins to doubt his Turbo Dueling talents. Can Jack kick things into overdrive?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Soul Solutions
programme.desc: Determined to defeat Dragan and his Nordic God, Jack summons a mighty new monster to the field that has enough fire power to send all of Dragan's life points up in smoke!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: When Nordic Gods Attack
programme.desc: With only a handful of life points remaining and the Nordic God, Thor, staring down at him, Jack gets set to take on his next opponent - Team Ragnarok's Broder!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Facility, Part 1
programme.desc: After being sent to The Facility, Yusei befriends an odd old man who duels with a treasure deck full of ancient mystic cards.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Facility, Part 2
programme.desc: Yusei duels the top dog at The Facility using Yanagi's treasure deck. Meanwhile, Jack learns about the mystery surrounding his Mark of the Crimson Dragon.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Fire It Up!
programme.desc: With Yusei still serving out his sentence at The Facility, Jack finds himself having to face off against former Turbo Duel Champion Hunter Pace in a rematch that could send Jack's career up in smoke.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Lockdown Duel, Part 1
programme.desc: After being sent to the Maximum Security Zone in The Facility, Yusei risks being permanently placed in lockdown when he decides to duel Chief Armstrong in order to win a pardon for his pal.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Lockdown Duel, Part 2
programme.desc: As the clash between Yusei and the Chief comes to a shocking conclusion, Yusei must figure out a way to win the battle before his life points get zapped to zero.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Take Back, Part 1
programme.desc: After being freed from the Facility, Yusei risks being re-incarcerated when he tries to take back his Duel Runner from Sector Security's vault.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Take Back, Part 2
programme.desc: With Officer Trudge in hot pursuit, Yusei looks to rev his game up before the long arm of the law grabs a hold of him for good!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A Duel to Remember
programme.desc: When Yusei can't remember his own name, he agrees to duel a pint-sized player named Leo in the hopes of getting his memory back.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Bloom of the Black Rose
programme.desc: As Leo and his pal Dexter venture into the narrows of New Domino City to find the mysterious duelist known as the Black Rose, Blister breaks out a plan to keep Yusei's friends in the Satellite Sector safe from Goodwin's goons.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Welcome to the Fortune Cup
programme.desc: The stage is set for the Fortune Cup as eight elite duelists vie for the chance to take on reigning champion Jack Atlas. However, for the Master of Ceremonies Rex Goodwin, it's not about who wins or loses.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Battle With the Black Rose
programme.desc: The second duel of the Fortune Cup is about to get under way as the mysterious duelist known as the Black Rose finds herself having to face off against a medieval menace named Sir Randsborg.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Surprise, Surprise!
programme.desc: With the first Turbo Duel of the Fortune Cup set to start, a surprise guest forces Yusei's competition to take an unexpected pit stop.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Return to the Spirit World, Part 1
programme.desc: Director Goodwin enlists the hypnotic powers of the Professor to expose Luna as a Signer and uncover the secrets she unknowingly knows of the Duel Monsters Spirit World.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Return to the Spirit World, Part 2
programme.desc: As the battle between the Professor and Luna continues, Luna looks to keep a promise she made to protect the Duel Monsters Spirit World, but in order for her to succeed, she must first break free of the hypnotic hold the Professor has on her.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Second Round Showdown, Part 1
programme.desc: The semifinals of the Fortune Cup are about to begin, and the first match of day two features Yusei going toe-to-toe with the tower of power - Greiger!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Second Round Showdown, Part 2
programme.desc: With no cards left in his hand and his life points about to get blasted by Greiger, Yusei has one draw left to take down this tower of power to keep in the hunt to duel Jack in the championship round.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Dueling Minds
programme.desc: In the second battle of the semifinals, Akiza squares off against the professional profiler Commander Koda, but with her tournament life on the line, can Akiza outplay an opponent who claims to know her every move?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Duel of the Dragons, Part 1
programme.desc: With the Fortune Cup Finale one win away, Yusei and Akiza get set to battle it out as Director Goodwin anxiously awaits the final Signer to reveal their Mark of the Dragon.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Duel of the Dragons, Part 2
programme.desc: As the back-and-forth battle between Akiza and Yusei rages on, Yusei is forced to unleash his mighty Stardust Dragon in order to stop Akiza's grisly garden from squeezing his life points into submission.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Fortune Cup Finale: Part 1
programme.desc: With the Fortune Cup Finale about to kick into overdrive, Jack decides to clear the air and reveal the truth behind his escape from the Satellite Sector.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Fortune Cup Finale, Part 2
programme.desc: With the finish line of the Fortune Cup fast approaching, Yusei and Jack find themselves on a collision course with destiny as they race to unlock the mystery behind the Crimson Dragon.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A Web of Deceit, Part 1
programme.desc: After defeating Jack to win the Fortune Cup Finale, Yusei is challenged to a Shadow Duel by an underground duelist whose mind has been taken over by the Dark Signers.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A Web of Deceit, Part 2
programme.desc: As the battle between Yusei and his robed rival rages on, Yusei must rely on his deck if he plans to survive this Shadow Duel and uncover the truth behind the Dark Signers sinister scheme to destroy the Satellite Sector.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Good Cop, Bad Cop
programme.desc: After agreeing to help Yusei meet with Director Goodwin, Officer Trudge unknowingly becomes one of the Dark Signers' drones and challenges a wounded Jack Atlas to a Shadow Duel.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Fight or Flight
programme.desc: Hoping to gain Yusei's trust, Director Goodwin decides to share with him the secrets behind the origin of the Satellite Sector and the ongoing war between Signer and Dark Signer.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Reunion Duel
programme.desc: After returning to the Satellite Sector, Yusei meets up with his old friend Crow and soon finds himself in a tag team Turbo Duel with Sector Security.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Dark Signs, Part 1
programme.desc: Yusei and Crow set off to confront the Dark Signers in an effort to stop them from destroying the Satellite Sector.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Dark Signs, Part 2
programme.desc: In an effort to save the Satellite Sector from being destroyed, Yusei agrees to face off against a former friend turned Dark Signer in a Shadow Duel.

programme.title: Hollidaysburg
programme.desc: A former prom king and his high school classmate begin an unlikely romance when they return from college on their first holiday break. From the filmmakers behind BREAKUP AT A WEDDING.

programme.title: School Dance
programme.desc: High school freshman Jason has found his dream girl, but there's just one problem: she doesn't know he exists. If he can win a spot on the school's hottest dance crew, he might have a shot in this comedy directed by Nick Cannon.

programme.title: Bikini Spring Break
programme.desc: A group of coeds from a small conservative college break out of their shells when their marching band bus breaks down in Ft. Lauderdale during Spring Break.

programme.title: King of the Ants
programme.desc: A young drifter discovers his true calling when he is hired to murder a man he has never met, leaving a trail of bodies in his wake.

programme.title: Legion of the Dead
programme.desc: When the mummified remains of an evil Egyptian queen are brought back to life, she resurrects an army of living dead to help fulfill the prophecy that promises her all the powers of the Underworld.

programme.title: CarGO
programme.desc: A young car learns the importance of family when he embarks on a mission to rescue his father – who’s been sent to Clunker Island to be repurposed as junk metal.

programme.title: Asteroid VS Earth
programme.desc: When a shower of massive meteors threatens Earth's inhabitants with extinction, the worlds greatest minds devise a dangerous plan that will tilt the planet off its axis to avoid the impact.

programme.title: Mega Shark vs Crocosaurus
programme.desc: The massive prehistoric shark has survived the last battle, and the world is again threatened when a new, more dangerous foe is discovered in the jungles of Africa.

programme.title: Sherlock Holmes
programme.desc: Sir Arthur Conan Doyle's famous detective faces the ultimate challenge when enormous monsters attack London.

programme.title: Trolland
programme.desc: Fenn the Troll hates the Troll pastime of pranking, and is teased so much for it that he runs away. But when a long-suffering park ranger starts capturing the other Trolls, it’s up to Fenn to rescue his family and friends - without pranking.

programme.title: Dragon
programme.desc: A princess must recruit the most brave and powerful swordsmen in the land with the sole purpose of vanquishing the dark wizard who terrorizes the kingdom with a giant, menacing dragon.

programme.title: Sex Pot
programme.desc: A pair of losers discover a legendary weed with aphrodisiac powers. "American Pie" meets "Half-Baked" in this screw ball comedy!

programme.title: Celebrity Sex Tape
programme.desc: A group of college nerds secretly record a washed up celebrity having sex and post the tape on the internet. When the publicity revives the actress's career, every B-list celebrity in Hollywood wants to star in the guys next "production.".

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Lockdown
programme.desc: Many urban explorers have encountered paranormal activity inside of the building, including child like figures, unexplained voices and strange knocking sounds. Will anything from the ghost dimension make contact?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Lockdown
programme.desc: Ghost Dimension's Bex and Sean investigate Norris Green Mansion. A 17th Century building, which is believed to hold some of the most haunted spirits in Liverpool. Will they make contact its ghostly entities tonight?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Lockdown
programme.desc: Ghost Dimension's Bex and Sean head to New Mills and investigate a home situated on the grounds of death and destruction from the bombings of WW2. Will any of the spirits lost in this disaster come forward and make contact during the investigation today?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Ghosts of Bolton Sea Cadets
programme.desc: The Ghost Dimension team heads to Bolton to check out the alleged haunting at Sea Cadets academy.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Haunted Weir Mill
programme.desc: The Ghost Dimension team visits Weir Mill, the oldest and most paranormally active mill in Stockport.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Haunting of New Mills Art Theatre Part 1
programme.desc: The Ghost Dimension team travels to Derbyshire to investigate the New Mills Arts Theatre. This quirky little building has played host to many famous acts and world-renowned plays but has a little-known secret in that it's allegedly haunted.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Haunting of New Mills Art Theatre Part 2
programme.desc: The Ghost Dimension Team is ready for act II at the New Mills Arts Theatre. With so much apparent activity happening at this unassuming theatre, the team just couldn't leave when so much more could happen.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Spirits at The Lord Eldon
programme.desc: The Ghost Dimension team travels to the old town of Knutsford, Cheshire to investigate the historic Lord Eldon Inn, hoping to contact the spirit of Sarah Ann Pollitt who is said to haunt the pub.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Sinister Happenings at The Village Farm Museum Part 1
programme.desc: The team heads to Lincolnshire to investigate the Village Farm Museum. This location looks out of place, being in the middle of a residential housing estate.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Sinister Happenings at The Village Farm Museum Part 2
programme.desc: This fascinating location sees a twist in the activity with Bex and Sean getting more than they bargained for.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Souls Seeking Solace Gotts Park Mansion
programme.desc: The team encounters a spirit member joining them on the thermal imaging camera and appearing to leave its ghostly hand print behind.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Long Lost Treasure at Jessops Old Mill and Auction House
programme.desc: The ghost dimension team visits Batley, West Yorkshire to investigate a location where it may not be the building that's haunted but the items that reside within.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: A Night at The Leeds Museum Part 1
programme.desc: Four floors of terror! Objects from around the world are at home in the museum, but what is attached to them, which now roams the floors and corridors after dark?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: A Night at The Leeds Museum Part 2
programme.desc: With activity sending the team into a spin on the top floor, is there something attached to the museum's main attraction, the mummy?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Lost Souls of One Melling Road
programme.desc: The team heads to Liverpool to help a restaurant uncover what could be haunting there. Bex and Sean encounter the spirit of a white lady in the private quarters.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Full House at Northwich Plaza and Bingo Hall
programme.desc: Bex and Sean head into Northwich, Cheshire to investigate a disused bingo hall. Bex braves a lone vigil, which she will never forget as a door seemingly opens on its own.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Last Orders at The Fleece Inn
programme.desc: The team heads to Elland to investigate ghostly-goings on in this haunted pub. It's not just the spirits behind the bar lurking here. Multiple hauntings, murders and death surround this public house.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Liverpool's Secret Haunted Mansion
programme.desc: Bex and Sean delve deep into Woolton Hall, a derelict mansion in Liverpool. They appear to be forced out of the building by an unknown force and it takes its toll on one of the team members.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Celebrity Special - The Black Horse in Pluckley Village
programme.desc: Bex and Sean are joined by reality TV star Charlie Doherty in the most haunted village in the UK and investigate the most haunted pub in the UK, The Black Horse.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: The Night Before The Storm
programme.desc: In this special episode, it's the night before Sean and Bex are joined by their celebrity guest and they check out The Black Horse in Pluckley Village to investigate the paranormal hauntings at the most haunted pub in the UK.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: High Spirits at The Gothic Mansion
programme.desc: Bex and Sean investigate a haunting inside a gothic mansion, that is said to be haunted by the former owner of the building.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: The Blues Haunting at The Winslow Hotel
programme.desc: Bex, Sean and the team head to Liverpool and investigate a very famous hotel, which Everton football club supporters have frequented for over 100 years and it would appear that some of the guests have never checked out.

programme.title: Monogamy
programme.desc: Increasingly anxious about his impending marriage to Nat (Rashida Jones) and bored with his day job as a wedding photographer, Theo (Chris Messina) begins a side business, clandestinely snapping voyeuristic photos of his clients.

programme.title: Rise Of The Chupacabras
programme.desc: A treasure map leads a group of unsuspecting townsfolk to the lair of vampire-like creatures known as the Chupacabras.

programme.title: Everyone Says I Love You
programme.desc: A New York girl sets her father up with a beautiful woman in a troubled marriage while her stepsister gets engaged. Starring: Woody Allen, Goldie Hawn, Julia Roberts, Edward Norton, Drew Barrymore, Natasha Lyonne, Natalie Portman.

programme.title: The Missing Person
programme.desc: John Rosow is a private detective hired to tail a man who's gone missing only to discover that returning the man to his life may not be the best solution for the man, or himself. Starring: Michael Shannon, Frank Wood, Amy Ryan.

programme.title: 21 Years
programme.desc: This documentary takes you on a behind the scenes tour into Linklater's style, skills, and motivation via his friends, actors, and other directors. Starring: Jack Black, Zac Efron, Matthew McConaughey, Julie Delpy, Miranda Cosgrove.

programme.title: The Whole Wide World
programme.desc: Set in the 1930s, a Texas schoolteacher falls in love with pulp writer Robert H. Howard. The two couldn't be more opposite; sharing almost nothing, but their uniquely passionate romance.

programme.title: From Nowhere
programme.desc: Nearing their high school graduation, three undocumented Bronx teenagers navigate the difficulties ofadolescence while living with the threat of being discovered by the authorities and their friends.

programme.title: The Last Time I Committed Suicide
programme.desc: Beat Poet Neal Cassady is pulled between two women, Mary, a teen temptress and J oan, his first true love. Starring: Thomas Jane, Keanu Reeves, Adrien Brody, John Doe, Claire Forlani.

programme.title: Legend Of Hell
programme.desc: An archaeologist discovers an ancient artifact and scroll which starts a series of events that kills her several times over in various time periods, past lives and locations.

programme.title: Iron Kid: Eiger the Patient
programme.desc: Marty has finally mastered the Fist and is put to the test against one of the General's elite robot warriors, Eiger the Patient. Meanwhile, Dr. Chen has finally revived the Gigantor and is ready to wipe the CDF out.

programme.title: Iron Kid: The Revolt of Kahn
programme.desc: Marty finally defeats Eiger and is ready to return when he senses Shadow fighting. He leaves to help, leaving Buttons to get to CDF headquarters with the Bullybots.

programme.title: Iron Kid: To the Iron Tower! Charge!
programme.desc: Marty finally arrives just in the nick of time to save the injured Kahn and fights his way through the General's forces to the Tower entrance, and at the same time, Ally has finally discovered a way to stop the Gigantor and leaves for the battlefield.

programme.title: Iron Kid: The Final Battle, Part 1
programme.desc: Marty finally arrives just in the nick of time to save the injured Kahn and fights his way through the General's forces to the Tower entrance, and at the same time, Ally has finally discovered a way to stop the Gigantor and leaves for the battlefield.

programme.title: Iron Kid: The Final Battle, Part 2
programme.desc: Marty finally faces off against the General. As a formidable opponent, Marty is forced to use all of his powers to fight the General. But even with the help of Gaff, Shadow, and Captain Magnum, the fight is not going to be easy.

programme.title: Pippi Longstocking: Pippi Returns to Villa Villekulla
programme.desc: Pippi Longstocking arrives in a small Swedish town to take up residence in her Villa.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: Popeye The Carpenter
programme.desc: Olive Oyl wants a picture hung on a wall in her house, so she calls in Popeye and Bluto to do this. However, Popeye and Bluto fight so much between themselves they end up wrecking Olive's house.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: The Ski's The Limit
programme.desc: Olive Oyl is teaching Swee'Pea how to skate. Popeye tried to learn also, but falls. Meanwhile Swee'Pea is in danger and Olive tries to rescue him but in vain. Popeye goes to their rescue and saves them both.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: Popeye The Sleepwalker
programme.desc: Popeye has spent seven days and sleepless nights on the high seas. When he returns he wants to call Olive Oyl but he falls asleep, and starts to sleep-walk onto the roof of the boat.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: A Whale of a Tale
programme.desc: Popeye's nephews can't sleep so he tells them a story about a man who was swallowed by a whale and who rescues a mermaid (Olive) from marrying King Neptune.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: Popeye Goes Sailing
programme.desc: Bluto invites Olive to go sailing with him, but because Popeye also wants to go along Bluto destroys his boat and sinks Popeye with it.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: A Seal with Appeal
programme.desc: Popeye and his nephews go fishing in his boat and they find a seal that they want to keep as a pet.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: Wilder than Usual Blue Yonder
programme.desc: Popeye takes Olive for a ride in his home made airplane but she doesn't like it.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: A Camping We Will Go
programme.desc: Popeye's nephews persuade him to take them camping. At the camp site, his nephews eat all the food and then complain they are still hungry.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: Take Me Out to the Brawl Game
programme.desc: Olive tries out for an all-male baseball team called the Burmingham Burgers.

programme.title: Popeye: New Adventures: Popeye Versus Machine

programme.title: Licence to Grill: Fancy Pants Dinner
programme.desc: It’s Rob’s turn to host the annual gourmet dinner. He heats up the grill and pulls together a delicious roasted tomato soup, grilled fillet mignon, sweet blue cheese stuffed pears, and some gourmet salads, and sides.

programme.title: Licence to Grill: Taste of India Celebration
programme.desc: Tales from Rob’s friend of his adventures in India entice Rob to grill up an Indian flavored feast. He puts together spicy mouth-watering dishes like lobster tails in curry butter, roasted curried potatoes, and decadent lamb steaks.

programme.title: Licence to Grill: Volleyball Tournament BBQ
programme.desc: Every year Rob and his friends enter a beach volleyball tournament and Rob is in charge of the pre-game lunch. He goes all light and healthy with an all fish & veggie menu.

programme.title: Licence to Grill: Volunteer Dinner Party
programme.desc: Rob hosts a bbq party full of incredible food as a sign of gratitude to his community. The brave souls rescued and thus silenced the neighbourhood cat that was stuck in his tree.

programme.title: Licence to Grill: Texas BBQ
programme.desc: Rob challenges some rodeo-riding friends from Texas to a race on horseback. He falls a little short leaving him in charge of making and paying for dinner.

programme.title: Licence to Grill: Successful Jump Celebration
programme.desc: Rob survives his first skydiving adventure and throws a celebration of life bbq for his instructor and class. Happy to have two feet on the ground Rob pulls together a feast of the best things in life.

programme.title: Licence to Grill: Non-Engagement Party
programme.desc: Rob grills up some romance for his commitment-phobic friend and his long waiting girlfriend with a non-engagement party.

programme.title: Licence to Grill: 80's Night at Rob's
programme.desc: Rob parties like its 1988 with a retro 80’s barbeque. With big hair, padded shoulders and bad dancing Rob’s friends are no square pegs.

programme.title: Licence to Grill: Boys Gone Fishing
programme.desc: Rob is back from a weekend fishing trip with the boys and it is time for a fish feast. Smoked Trout, whole Trout, grilled smallmouth bass, smoked veggie salsa and saffron rice are on the barbeque.

programme.title: Licence to Grill: Hot Tub Party
programme.desc: It is time for Rob’s annual Hot Tub Extravaganza! His friends sun by the pool and soak in the hot tub while Rob fires up the grill and make some delicious chicken kebabs.

programme.title: One World Kitchen
programme.desc: Colourful host Natalia Machado makes mouth-watering dishes from her home country of Argentina like Duck Carpaccio and Churros.

programme.title: One World Kitchen
programme.desc: Endearing host Vanessa Gianfrancesco whips up a traditional Italian four-course meal.

programme.title: Hunter: The Avenging Angel
programme.desc: A mentally disturbed surveillance expert follows Hunter for weeks. He emulates Hunter and wants to be his equal in fighting crime and "cleaning up the city".

programme.title: Hunter: Snow Queen Part 1
programme.desc: McCall's prime informant in a case against a drug merchant is a cocaine supplier who's being extradited as a murder witness by a policeman who seems intent on killing her.

programme.title: Hunter: Snow Queen Part 2
programme.desc: Dee Dee's in danger as she moves closer to exposing a ruthless drug dealer. Hunter fights to keep a rogue policeman from killing a material witness.

programme.title: Hunter: Beach Boys
programme.desc: The Beach Boy arrives in Los Angeles from Hawaii, picks up his luggage and heads for his car. The next day, he arrives at Eddy Marks' house and shoots him down in his kitchen.

programme.title: Hunter: Guilty
programme.desc: Hunter and McCall go after a convicted murderer who is back out on the street and has vowed to kill the jurors who convicted him.

programme.title: Hunter: The Last Kill
programme.desc: Hunter and McCall go after a contract killer who is making hits throughout the city in order to ingratiate himself with a criminal kingpin in order to kill him.

programme.title: Hunter: Killer in a Halloween Mask
programme.desc: Hunter and McCall become involved in a string of bizarre murders when they're assigned as technical advisors for a television show.

programme.title: Hunter: Rape & Revenge - Part 1
programme.desc: When McCall is raped by a South American diplomat who's immune from prosecution, Hunter turns renegade and follows the man to his homeland.

programme.title: Hunter: Rape & Revenge - Part 2
programme.desc: Against departmental orders, Hunter goes to South America to stalk a diplomat who raped McCall.

programme.title: Hunter: Six Million Dollar Misunderstanding
programme.desc: A security guard-turned-thief loses the money he stole and searches for it with Hunter and McCall in close pursuit.

programme.title: Hunter: The Big Fall
programme.desc: Hunter and McCall realize they're attracted to each other as they protect an endangered witness who's set to testify before a grand jury.

programme.title: Hunter: Waiting for Mr. Wrong
programme.desc: Hunter becomes involved with a beautiful model he suspects of complicity in a jewelry robbery.

programme.title: Hunter: Think Blue
programme.desc: Hunter helps a policeman who is framed for the murder of his wife.

programme.title: Hunter: Blow Up
programme.desc: Hunter is frustrated in his pursuit of a package bomber whose ruthless methods are being used to systematically kill the participants in the man's trial.

programme.title: Hunter: War Zone
programme.desc: Hunter and McCall work to stop a brigade of suburban mercenaries plotting to break a drug dealer out of prison.

programme.title: Hunter: Burned
programme.desc: Hunter and McCall are given 72 hours to find an attorney who falsified his death.

programme.title: Hunter: Scrap Metal
programme.desc: When a dying contract killer confesses he was once paid to kill Hunter's father, Hunter goes in pursuit of the true murderer.

programme.title: Hunter: Fagin 1986
programme.desc: When Rick Hunter, a renegade cop who takes justice into his own hands, partners with the stunning and rebellious Sgt. McCall, they set out to crack down on L.A.'s slimiest criminals.

programme.title: Hunter: 62 Hours of Terror
programme.desc: When Rick Hunter, a renegade cop who takes justice into his own hands, partners with the stunning and rebellious Sgt. McCall, they set out to crack down on L.A.'s slimiest criminals.

programme.desc: The recruits must execute elegant meals for two, sit down to eat with their chef and defend their dishes. The losing recruits are eliminated.

programme.desc: The final four compete in a "culinary decathlon" to test their knowledge thus far.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Best of the Worst

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Two-A-Day
programme.desc: The recruits face two challenges in one day, beginning with breakfast for Bobby and Anne.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Eat, Pray, Love
programme.desc: To determine who will compete in the final, the final four recruits cook for their loved ones in a blind tasting challenge.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Timer's Up

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Psychopathic killers lurk in society, mostly acting alone. Sometimes fate brings them into contact with another person who shares their cold power to kill.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: We want to believe that all women would give their lives to protect their children. But there are horrifying cases when a mother will turn against her natural instinct and kill her own flesh and blood.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: The mind of a female killer is shaped by a complex cocktail of influences. Do people become that way, driven by horrendous events in their lives? Or are some killers born bad?

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Blood ties are strong ties, sometimes strong enough to pull a person into a murderous conspiracy. When a family member wields his or her power, the result can be death.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: The path towards revenge can sometimes lead to murder. It can be quick, fiery and violent. It can also be a dish served cold, the product of a calm, calculated plot.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: While their sisters chose a life of sensible, suburban motherhood, these deadly women chose a life of crime. They lived with the thrills, the danger and the deadly consequences of being outlaws.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Greed is one of the oldest motives for murder, and these deadly women are no exception: they’ll do anything to satisfy their need for cash. This is the dangerous world of the fortune hunters.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Under His Control
programme.desc: These are love stories with bleak, bloody endings. Blinded by desire, obsessed and malleable, some women fall into lethal relationships with dangerous, controlling men.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Secrets and Lies
programme.desc: Behind their friendly smiles, deadly women hide histories of bloodshed and murder.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Love Gone Wrong
programme.desc: Love can be beautiful, love can be blind and love can be deadly. Desire and jealousy are powerful forces driving women to dark and horrifying places in their minds.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Married to Murder
programme.desc: To the outside world, their marriages seemed happy. But behind closed doors, there was no domestic bliss. These women wanted out, but getting a divorce wasn’t their preferred option.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Teen Killers
programme.desc: They were too young to drink or vote but they were not too young to commit the most brutal of crimes. Some were driven by pure curiosity: how would it feel to take a life?

programme.title: Deadly Women: Love to Death
programme.desc: Love and money are a beautiful marriage, for the lucky ones they create a life of happiness and ease. Unless the love is of money, the bride is a killer, and the groom their victim.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Kill Their Own
programme.desc: A mother's most basic instinct is to protect her children, to put their needs above her own desire for money, freedom and men. But these deadly women break that sacred bond when they turn against that natural instinct and kill their own offspring.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Obsession
programme.desc: Deciphering what causes minds to corkscrew out of control is the complex work of the criminal profiler. Obsessions can take many forms: beauty, devotion, ego and power.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Hearts of Stone
programme.desc: Deadly Women are not always the ones you expect. They are not the strangers lurking in the dark, they are a young mother, a supportive wife and a grandmother - all killers. Behind their loving masquerade lies a wake of family horror and pain.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Greed
programme.desc: Known as “black widows,” these women kill their spouses, lovers and children for profit. Murder for them becomes a business. Their trade is murder. Their profit? Blood money.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Crimes of revenge are usually single acts of passion. A brew of hatred and restitution boils over in a manic moment of fury. Once caught, revenge killers usually display remorse and atonement.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: No one doubts a woman’s capacity to love, but sometimes lust can turn lethal. In the ultimate fatal attraction, "Deadly Women" looks at cases of murder driven by obsessive love.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: A rifle in a shopping mall, a syringe of potassium chloride and a syringe of insulin, each in the hands of a mentally disturbed woman, lead to the tragic end of many lives.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Obsession
programme.desc: Power is a responsibility as well as a privilege. But in the wrong hands, power can corrupt. For former Deputy Attorney General for the State of Delaware, losing sight of his sworn oath to uphold justice could prove lethal.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Terror In Disguise
programme.desc: Banks use a variety of devices to discourage would-be robbers: security cameras, silent alarms, and exploding dye packs. But when an elusive bank robber targeted Seattle's banks, none of these precautions were effective.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Trail
programme.desc: The disappearance of young women triggered a search that spanned the Pacific Northwest. A massive media campaign failed to locate the drifter, who first charmed then killed them. As investigators followed his trail, he always stayed one step ahead.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Predator
programme.desc: In the early 1990's, Washington, D.C., became the murder capital of the nation. Few were left untouched by gang violence, which was ignited by the drug trade. By 1994, that violence would strike at the very heart of law enforcement.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Backstage Murder
programme.desc: In the 1980's, two partners created a nightclub that would bring them wealth and international fame. The male strip club phenomenon promised female patrons fun and excitement. But the bright lights hid a dark side.

programme.title: Duck Dynasty: Toad to Perdition
programme.desc: When Willie and his brothers spend too much time frog hunting, their wives challenge them to a "frogging" competition.

programme.title: Duck Dynasty: Wild Wild West Monroe
programme.desc: When Jase and Jep get into an argument over which of them is the rightful heir to their grandfather's old rifle, they decide to settle the argument with a marksmanship contest. Meanwhile, Willie and Korie help Rebecca prepare for her trip to Taiwan.

programme.title: Duck Dynasty: Half in the Bag

programme.desc: Witness Dave Thomas' Bob Hope and Andrew Dice Clay impressions. Plus: Buddy Hackett tells jokes and Teresa Ganzel also appears.

programme.title: The Johnny Carson Show: Comic Legends Of The '90s - Drew Carey (1/10/92)
programme.desc: Comedian and actor Drew Carey talks about cold weather and global warming. Fellow guests are David Steinberg and Regis Philbin.

programme.title: The Johnny Carson Show: Comic Legends Of The '60s - Joan Rivers (12/31/75)

programme.title: The Johnny Carson Show: Comic Legends Of The '60s - Dom Deluise (3/6/73)
programme.desc: Dom Deluise on earthquakes, Bruno Vailati on sharks and Sally Kellerman on the Queen of England highlight this episode. Plus, Ronnie Schell does stand-up.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Three's Company
programme.desc: This fugitive is hard to pin down in Honolulu's downtown district, moving from hostel to hotel to apartment high-rise. But as the hunt evolves, Dog discovers that this alleged burglar isn't the only family member wanted by the law.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Strip Search
programme.desc: When a stripper goes on the lam, Dog has to bring her in. It's a tough job but somebody has to do it. Thankfully for the team, Lady Luck is presiding over the posse tonight.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Secret Places
programme.desc: When Leland learns that one of his clients with a reputation for stealing has lost her co-signer and could be ready to run, Dog and the crew hop a plane to the Big Island.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Wrong Turn
programme.desc: Dog's target today seems to have a taste for drugs and a record of reckless driving. The hunt has deep emotional resonance for the team because today is the anniversary of the fatal car accident of Dog's daughter Barbara Katie.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Easy Rider
programme.desc: What looks like a routine pick-up turns into a complicated case of betrayal, deceit, as well as quality nail care as Dog and company track down a fugitive alleged to be an abusive boyfriend with one too many friends in his close knit community.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Midnight Run
programme.desc: This fugitive has a bad reputation and a knack for running from the law. The pursuit has Dog and team traveling through an urban dystopia of suspicion, false leads and mistrust.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Hunt for Santa
programme.desc: Dog decides he needs to help his son Garry believe in Santa Claus again. So now the Dog, with a posse expanded to include his children and grandchildren, sets off on a hunt through the Colorado Rockies for Santa Claus himself!

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Call Waiting
programme.desc: Dog's target for today has been in trouble with the law since he was a juvenile. And he seems willing to use any trick in the system to avoid capture by Dog. In this match of wits, will Dog prevail?

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Kid Stuff
programme.desc: A fugitive from justice is on the lam and it's Dog's job to find him. When they hit the last known address they discover he already has pulled up stakes and left no forwarding address. The posse's one hope is to locate his girlfriend.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: All My Children
programme.desc: For a guy who started life as a free spirited outlaw-biker Dog has certainly turned into a family man. His children touch everything he does today, from searching for the perfect gift for his daughter Cecily's birthday to hunting a fugitive.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Welcome to the Jungle
programme.desc: The hunt for an elusive and clever criminal takes Dog through the world of a bantam fighting cock, a pregnant daughter, and a jungle safe house go together. And don't forget the mopeds as well as a group of hostile squatters on government land!

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Bounty Baby
programme.desc: What's a father to do? When the cops ask Dog for help tracking down a renegade teen with a history of running hard, Baby Lyssa, eight months pregnant and counting, insists on joining the hunt. Can Dog keep his daughter safe and catch his man?

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Rain Check
programme.desc: For Dog and Beth it's not only another day in paradise, it's their anniversary. Beth is hoping for a romantic dinner with her man, but she knows only too well that for Dog work always comes first.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Love on the Run
programme.desc: Today Dog finds himself looking for more than one fugitive. He starts the day looking for a woman who has skipped out on her court date. But he soon learns that she has teamed up with a woman whose criminal exploits have attracted the local media.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Jump Start
programme.desc: Dog gave a break to a young man with a drug problem who promised to enter drug rehab. But this commitment to rehabilitation seems to have ended when he bolted from the car on the way to the drug treatment center and went on the run.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Ice Man
programme.desc: Dog's latest fugitive doesn't think small when it comes to illegal drugs: he was carrying almost a pound of meth when he was arrested. Now he's on the run with his pregnant girlfriend on the high plains of Colorado.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Trouble in Paradise
programme.desc: Dog is back in Hawaii and tracking a dangerous fugitive through the jungles of the Big Island. Their prey is being protected by a ring of family and friends that Dog must forcefully confront to bring in his man.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Baby's Back in Town
programme.desc: Dog tries to nab a fugitive, named Wayne, by calling and telling him that he's won a new vacuum cleaner and he should stick around to get it. Dog then sends his daughter, Lyssa, to "deliver" the vacuum cleaner and lure Wayne out of his house.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Surprise! Surprise!
Dog The Bounty Hunter: No Ice in Paradise
programme.desc: Dog and his team fight the war on ice-crystal methamphetamine-on many fronts. They appear on a special anti-drug float in a parade. Then they go after bail-jumping Pana, a convicted drug dealer.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Fathers in Law
programme.desc: Hunting down a fugitive known as "Bozo," Dog gets help from an unexpected source, Bozo's father-in-law.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Bosco the Clown
programme.desc: Dog and the team get a big surprise after they track down Bosco, a fugitive who they believe is addicted to methamphetamines. They discover he's off drugs, settling into a normal life with a new girlfriend, and is very friendly.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Brother's Keeper
programme.desc: Leland has a full plate of fugitives in Kona, and the whole family heads to the Big Island to help.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Mama's Boys
programme.desc: Dog visits his mother's grave for inspiration before heading out to find Frankie, a violent fugitive hiding in the jungle. The spirit of Ma Chapman seems to help when Dog finds an unusual ally; Frankie's mother.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Lost in Paradise
programme.desc: Dog lectures high school students about the dangers of drugs before going after Joseph, a dangerous fugitive who won't be easy to capture.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Coaching Day
programme.desc: Dog takes the day off to try his hand at coaching, and assigns Tim and Leland to track down a dangerous fugitive on their own. Can the boys prove they can handle it?

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Women of Waikiki
programme.desc: The boys get distracted by the bikini-clad lovelies on Waikiki when they hunt for Lucy, a homeless, alcoholic fugitive. Beth is amused by the boys, but this is serious business: Tim will have to pay the bond if Lucy isn't caught.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: To Capture One's Own
programme.desc: Dog faces a tough personal and professional situation when he must hunt down his friend, Ili, who has helped him on many busts. But now Ili's on the other side of the law, and now Dog must bring her in.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Big Bags and Boxers
programme.desc: Dog is out to make two grabs on two islands in one day. Part of the team is goes to Kona to nab a woman who skipped her court date. Meanwhile, Dog and the others hunt Patrick, a fugitive who's fighting in an Extreme Boxing event on the Big Island.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Cats & Dogs
programme.desc: Dog has only a few days to catch a woman nicknamed Cats or forfeit Beth's $10,000 bond. But it won't be easy - Cats is eight months pregnant, so Dog will have to lure her in rather than risk a violent grab.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Destiny Love
programme.desc: Dog is in for a big surprise after he catches a fugitive named Jonaven in a sting operation.
